headline: Three Reasons Why RL is Risky and One Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Ralph Lauren’s 34.2% return over the past six months has outpaced the S&P 500 by 25.4%, and its stock price has climbed to $231 per share. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
